Rules & restrictions for the m-TDT tool

*****

* Load files 

- The Load button runs summary.R
- Detect all ped, map, phen files extensions (done)
- cannot run analysis if you did not load your files first
- automatically suggest the corresponding map file when a ped file is selected


* Chooose options

- When Single-Marker is enabled -> disable nbsim
- detect number of columns for the phenfile (nc) and propose from 1 to (nc-2)
- detect number of cores (n) and propose from 1 to (n-1) cores
- nbsim from 1 to 10 (is there a rule for this option?)
- Run Analysis button runs run_analysis.R

* Output 

- Clear console button 
